Description: A habit change app to help people lose weight and keep it off without dieting. *Launched at The Founder's Institute.
Full Description: Dieting to meet your health goals? No, thank you! It’s stressful, hard to maintain, and doesn’t always produce the results. We all know the feeling of making great progress for a week, being active and eating well, only to slide back into old habits when the weekend comes. That’s why we created a science-based app to help you lose weight by building better eating habits, not by dieting. EXPERTS INSTEAD OF DIETING. Team up with our expert nutrition coaches (real human support) to stop dieting and start building healthy eating habits, one step at a time. LIVE A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE. Lose weight and keep it off, for good. We’ll help you improve your relationship with food, eat more mindfully and build better eating habits which last a lifetime. LEARN WHY YOU EAT. We help you gain awareness of why you’re eating by identifying emotional, situational and cultural food triggers. Your Believe Nutrition coach will then help you create better eating behaviors around such triggers. Once you consistently repeat these behaviors, you’ll form new and positive eating habits. PHOTO TRACKING INSTEAD OF CALORIE COUNTING. Say goodbye to counting calories and macros. Simply take a photo of what you eat and log it in your food journal. Your Believe Nutrition coach will then share their feedback, make recommendations and celebrate your small wins. NO JUDGEMENT. JUST EMPOWERMENT. Flexible: we give you the ability to eat all the foods you enjoy and crave. No food restriction. Accountability: we’ll hold you accountable and keep you motivated at every step of the way. On-the-go: we’ll help you eat well confidently to feel your best wherever you are – at home, in restaurants or even while traveling. WHO ARE THE BELIEVE NUTRITION COACHES? The Believe Nutrition network has highly qualified dietitians and nutritionists who have attained a formal degree in dietetics, nutrition or a similar field. Our coaches have experience with weight management, women's health, food relationships, mindful eating and more.

Description: Pre-set Appointments Outside Sales
Full Description: Lexicon Senior Healthcare (LSH) is a new 2011 marketing arm of a publically-traded Fortune 500 Company with assets under management exceeding $32,000,000,000!  Although seemingly similar to competitor marketing firms selling our type of products, Lexicon specializes in distributing healthcare supplemental benefit products as first-offer to the senior citizen market. Like similar competitor marketers, LSH salespeople (referred to as Consultants) are provided with daily preset appointments Tuesday through Friday (no cold-calling!), but the quality of the LSH preset appointment is of a much higher quality.  LSH initially trains its new consultants only to sell the highest-demand, easiest to sell, most simple senior healthcare product, called Medicare Supplement. After placing this business, LSH further trains its consultants to sell additional products to their existing clients, while still allowing all of their consultants to continue on daily preset appointments at their own discretion. In addition, LSH consultants after having sold only $50,000 of Medicare Supplement (usually a 2 month period for an entry-level consultant to accomplish this level of production) are allowed to make their own decisions as to what days and what locations they wish to have preset appointments and are also given the option to step into a management role immediately.  Further differing itself similar competitors, in as soon as 6 weeks, all LSH consultants' commissions are markedly increased from their entry-level commission, as strict/regimented management of LSH consultants post $50,000 Medicare Supplement production is eliminated, training meetings are now optional, training travel is no longer necessary, they are selling far more of their appointments (as the learning curve is over!) earning a higher revenue margin to Lexicon per appointment provided, etc... Bottom-line, a jump in their commission level can now be made because a larger spread of commission dollars are available. Thus, the Lexicon marketing arm, unlike others, shares this higher dollar margin back to the consultant in the form of a generous commission level increase versus retaining it for higher corporate gains. Lexicon wants to not only care for, train, and support each consultant individually, but they understand a key fundamental ingredient to retaining a consultant is to make him/her a fortune quicker in upfront commission income as well as with immediate monthly residual income!  The most exciting part of selling for LSH is that their supplemental products are not affected by the economy whatsoever. To the contrary, individual consultant average sales volume is continuing to rise even in the midst of a down economy. This is simply due to the rapidly increasing number of babyboom generation seniors entering the marketplace. They have Lexicon's products on the forefront of their mind as they approach age 65 as they need a product to take over their healthcare costs where Medicare leaves behind... LSH sales are literally sky-rocketing!  This creates the opportunity for a LSH consultant to build a fortune of clients on the books paying them an increasingly "stacking" monthly residual income and the opportunity to expand their horizons into additional senior products (and underage supplement products) with the virtual immediate option of leaping into a management role and earning more income from subordinate new consultants whom they initially train and manage through their learning curve. With Lexicon Senior Healthcare, THERE IS NO LIMIT TO HOW MUCH AN INDIVIDUAL SALESPERSON CAN EARN!!!

Full Description: The need for FastTrends.com became apparent to Tom Andrews and Eric Henry as they grew their licensed t-shirt company, Logotel, from startup to trend-setting industry leader. Tom and Eric saw that every link in the licensing chain, from licensor to retailer, was missing out on potentially valuable opportunities because each step of the licensing process was so time consuming and inefficient. They realized that today's technologies could be used to reduce lag times, identify and contact potential strategic partners, build lasting and profitable relationships, provide promotional opportunities, deliver important industry news, and track all of the licensing processes on a product by product basis. But they also knew that this $140+ billion a year industry was built on personal relationships and that it would not, could not, and should not be turned into an impersonal "technology business" with the click of a mouse. That's why they envisioned a company where personally delivered member services would form the backbone for an industry leading array of easy-to-use, customizable, online tools developed to help each individual member expand their own segment of the licensing industry. FastTrends.com is the realization of that vision.

Description: Footprint Worldwide is a comprehensive China-centric consulting and branded entertainment company.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Footprint Worldwide is a branded entertainment company, specializing in creating and producing content for distribution in China through our vast distribution network. Based in Los Angeles and Beijing, Footprint marries global brands to music, sports, games, TV and other entertainment to create new content that is localized for the marketplace. We help brands reach their desired demographic targets in new and innovative ways. As opposed to straight advertising or product placement, the concept of brand integration is still in its infancy in China. Footprint is leading the way to a more effective and greater opportunity for brand development in the world's newest and most exciting emerging market. Focusing on new media and alternative distribution, Footprint's robust distribution network encompasses the most desired target demographics in China and offers maximum penetration to over 600 million individual users. Our distribution channels include online portals, social networks, mobile networks, online music stores, television, radio, and a closed-circuit high quality streaming college network that reaches 25 million 18-22 year old college students across 2,000 campuses nationwide. Our management team has been on the ground in China for nearly 7 years in the music, culture and entertainment industries. The company holds a deep understanding of the marketplace, cultural practices, and carries with it an extensive and trusted relationship network throughout the country. The team has completed numerous projects throughout the years including Midem 2008's "Year of China", together with the Ministry of Culture; a short-form documentary on the history of skateboarding in China; and globally publishing and distributed the largest Chinese music catalog in the world. Additionally, they have vast experience developing new media initiatives with major brands, such as McDonald's, Kroger, and Macy's. The combined extensive experience in the Chinese market drives our creative strategies to capture the hearts and minds of a complex market and ever changing consumer landscape. Footprint has an entire slate of projects scheduled for 2009 including new localized and innovative branded Linkin Park content for widespread distribution, an educational music channel designed specifically for Chinese college students, and a long-form documentary and branded programmed channel on Chinese action sports.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment
